 is the sixth largest corporation by market capitalization in the swiss market index as of  richemont is the secondlargest luxury goods company in the world after lvmh contents  history  organization  ownership and control  investments  subsidiaries  joint ventures  other investments  former investments  website blocking  notes  references  external links historyedit johann rupert founded compagnie financière richemont sa in  when he spun off the international assets of rembrandt group ltd now remgro limited a south africabased company founded in the s by his father dr anton rupert the luxury goods investments of rembrandt group combined with rothmans international formed the initial group of richemont subsidiaries according to a state ordered investigation conducted by ciex and published in  rembrandt played a part in the bankorp deal in which several leading south african financial bodies conspired to steal r billion from the state during apartheid the report claims rembrandt should pay back roughly r billion for its involvement in march  richemont and polo ralph lauren inc announced the formation of a  joint venture the polo ralph lauren watch and jewelry company sàrl in october  the group divested all of its remaining interests in the tobacco industry as of november update compagnie financière richemont sa is the sixth largest corporation by market capitalization in the swiss market index as of  richemont is the secondlargest luxury goods company in the world after lvmh organizationedit compagnie financière richemont sa organizes its business activities into three operating divisions jewellery maisons specialist watchmakers and other businesses cartier van cleef  arpels and giampiero bodino constitute the jewellery maisons the specialist watchmakers group is composed of a lange  söhne baume  mercier iwc schaffhausen jaegerlecoultre officine panerai piaget roger dubuis vacheron constantin and the joint venture with the ralph lauren watch  jewelry co the other businesses division includes azzedine alaïa chloé dunhill lancel montblanc peter millar purdey and shanghai tang ownership and controledit the largest significant shareholder of compagnie financière richemont sa is compagnie financière rupert a swiss company that holds shares controlled and principally owned by johann rupert compagnie financière rupert owns  class b shares of compagnie financière richemont sa representing  of the equity and  of the voting rights johann rupert and compagnie financière rupert also hold  class a shares or a share equivalents as of the end of march  investmentsedit subsidiariesedit the following companies are wholly owned subsidiaries of compagnie financière richemont sa unless otherwise noted a lange  söhne — watches based in glashütte germany azzedine alaïa — womens fashions based in paris france baume  mercier — watches based in geneva switzerland cartier — jewellery and watches based in paris france chloé — womens clothing based in paris france dunhill — mens clothing watches and leather goods based in london united kingdom giampiero bodino — high jewellery based in milan italy iwc schaffhausen — watches based in schaffhausen switzerland lancel — leathergoods based in paris france and with as of february  marianne romestain as chief executive officer jaegerlecoultre — watches based in le sentier switzerland montblanc — writing instruments and watches based in hamburg germany officine panerai — watches based in florence italy peter millar — mens and womens apparel based in durham nc usa piaget — jewellery watches based in geneva switzerland purdey — firearms ammunition based in london united kingdom roger dubuis — watches based in geneva switzerland shanghai tang — mens and womens fashions based in hong kong vacheron constantin — watches based in geneva switzerland van cleef  arpels — jewellery watches based in paris france joint venturesedit ralph lauren watch and jewelry co  — watches jewellery based in geneva switzerland other investmentsedit yoox netaporter group — ecommerce based in milan italy former investmentsedit in  the group sold its minority stake in vivendi representing its exit from all previous media interests which had included nethold and canal richemont acquired british clothing retailer hackett limited in  on  june  richemont announced its sale to spanish investment company torreal scr sa richemont and mimi so formed a joint venture in   richemonts first investment in an american brand in  richemont requested to become the majority partner of the joint venture mimi so declined and purchased richemonts stake in the venture in  richemont spun off all of its nonluxury goods businesses principally richemonts stake in british american tobacco into a newly formed separately traded holding company reinet investments sca in  the netaporter group was merged with the yoox group in an allshare transaction richemont is the largest shareholder in the enlarged group website blockingedit in october  the first blocking order against trademark infringing consumer goods was passed against the major uk isps by richemont cartier international and montblanc to block several domains selling trademark infringing products notesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l richemont annual report and accounts  pdf richemontcom retrieved  june    a b c d e f richemont company announcement issued on  may  pdf richemont retrieved  may    a b european sales help luxury group richemont balance a decline in asia  remgro   international directory of company histories   richemont history including significant investments and divestments retrieved  january    domisse  esterhuyse  pp   not just absa other companies named in apartheidera state looting report retrieved    richemont and polo ralph lauren announce the formation of the polo ralph lauren watch and jewellery company richemontcom retrieved  march    richemont to spin off its tobacco holdings the wall street journal retrieved  august    swiss exchange   richemont company